item.description:
kosli version # Print the version of Kosli CLI.
Synopsis # Print the version of Kosli CLI. The output will look something like this: version.BuildInfo{Version:&quot;v0.0.1&quot;, GitCommit:&quot;fe51cd1e31e6a202cba7dead9552a6d418ded79a&quot;, GitTreeState:&quot;clean&quot;, GoVersion:&quot;go1.16.3&quot;}
Version is the semantic version of the release. GitCommit is the SHA for the commit that this version was built from. GitTreeState is &quot;clean&quot; if there are no local code changes when this binary was built, and &quot;dirty&quot; if the binary was built from locally modified code.
